I have a lot of cells with a textfield inside, appearing and disappearing on a field. So, when I create a new TextField inside CellView, I need to dispose it on cell.destroy(). So, it looks like:

In constructor:

``` ActionScript
_label = new TextField(100, 100, "", "numbers", -1, 0xFFFFFF);
_label.batchable = true;
_container.addChild(_label);
```

In cell.destroy():

``` ActionScript
_label.removeFromParent(true);
_label = null;
```

It was not GC'ed accurately, I added a line before:

``` ActionScript
_label.removeChildren(0, -1, true);
_label.removeFromParent(true);
_label = null;
```

